abstract: French swimmer Aurelie Muller wins women’s 10-kilometer open-water race at world swimming championships; other results noted.
lead_paragraph: Muller won by 2.4 seconds in Kazan, Russia, and finished in a time of 1 hour 58 minutes 4.3 seconds.

headline.main: France’s Aurélie Muller Wins Women’s Open-Water 10K
